# Next.js Architecture

- Default to Server Components. Client components only for browser APIs, events, or local state.
- Use App Router file conventions intentionally (`page`, `layout`, `loading`, `error` when needed).
- Data fetching in Server Components; Server Actions for mutations with Zod validation.
- Route Handlers sparingly (webhooks, proxies, special headers).
- Caching: request memoization, Data Cache (`revalidate` / tags), Full Route Cache for static routes.
- Session refresh via `src/proxy.ts` — not `middleware.ts`.

